OL,6,F2009 - Drinks industry body intervenes
OL,7,Fover Speedball beer
OL,9,FIn one of many disputes with the
OL,10,Falcohol industry marketing self-
OL,11,Fregulatory body, BrewDog was branded
OL,12,F"grossly irresponsible" for naming one
OL,13,Fof its beers "Speedball".
OL,15,FThe Portman Group said in a ruling
OL,16,Fthat it was "entirely inappropriate"
OL,17,Fto name an alcoholic drink after the
OL,18,F"extremely dangerous practice" of
OL,19,Fcombining heroin and cocaine.
